<div id="review_1466357532" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1466357532" />
    <a title="Paul E. Morph" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/44824883-paul-e-morph"><img alt="Paul E. Morph" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1611008105p2/44824883.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1466357532?book_show_action=true">Feb 08, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Paul E. Morph" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Paul E. Morph" href="/user/show/44824883-paul-e-morph">Paul E. Morph</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780670845453" href="/book/show/24858652-a-place-of-greater-safety">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/44824883-paul-e-morph?shelf=books-read-in-2017">books-read-in-2017</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1466357532" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13621178320930517076">I don&apos;t read a great deal of historical fiction; in fact, I&apos;m struggling to think of any other historical fiction I&apos;ve read off the top of my head, but that could just be the premature senility. I bought this one because I&apos;ve been meaning to read some Hilary Mantel for awhile, to see what all the fuss was about, and this book was Audible&apos;s book of the day.<br/><br/>It&apos;s certainly a well written book, exploring the French Revolution on a very human, nuts and bolts level (although there&apos;s unavoidably a sign</span>
  <span id="freeText13621178320930517076" style="display:none">I don't read a great deal of historical fiction; in fact, I'm struggling to think of any other historical fiction I've read off the top of my head, but that could just be the premature senility. I bought this one because I've been meaning to read some Hilary Mantel for awhile, to see what all the fuss was about, and this book was Audible's book of the day.<br /><br />It's certainly a well written book, exploring the French Revolution on a very human, nuts and bolts level (although there's unavoidably a significant amount of politics as well). I found it very engaging and I finished it a lot faster than I thought I would, which is always a good sign.<br /><br />The only thing is, it mainly engaged me on an intellectual level. I really struggled to connect with any of the people whose lives were chronicled here on an emotional level, which amazes me, really, considering what they were living through. Perhaps the fault was on my side, but a lack of empathy isn't something I usually struggle with.<br /><br />I'd still say this book is a great success as a historical chronicle but I was hoping for more heart and less head. It definitely hasn't put me off reading more of Mantel's work, though.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13621178320930517076" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


